Author: MkGregor
Title: [ANN] [ICO]ğŸ”¥ BITCOINUS - Ecommerce payment processorğŸ”¥
Body: A great article from our Advisor - Dylan Sharkey, Senior Advisor at Provoco, Ex LinkedIn Head of Sales for MENA, Enterprise Ireland alumnus.      The heir to PayPalâ€™s throne - can FinTech startup Bitcoinus succeed where Stripe failed?  The first quarter of 2018 was notable for two major announcements in the ecommerce and payments space.  The most promising potential usurper to PayPalâ€™s crown; Stripe announced in January that they would completely phase out Bitcoin payments on their platform by April, citing high transaction costs and slow speeds. It seems a shame that the innovative disruptor founded by the precocious Irish Collison Brothers would take a step back rather than find a technical or operational solution.  A month later Coinbase, the popular consumer focused cryptocurrency wallet launched Coinbase Commerce enabling merchants to accept multiple cryptocurrencies directly into a user-controlled wallet. While not a truly decentralized solution, Coinbaseâ€™s approach is not hosted to the merchants have full control over their wallets and currency.  All aspects of finance are being impacted by Blockchain technologies. This should result, not only in significant cost reduction for market participants, but will transform financial services and online commerce as we know it. Cryptocurrency will do for payments what electronic mail did for communication.  Beyond FinTechâ€Šâ€”â€ŠPower to the Participants 2018 will be remembered as the year that Crypto Payments went mainstream, massively disrupting the ecommerce space. The main incumbents, Paypal and Stripe have yet to embrace Cryptocurrencies while the only other serious contenders; Coinbase Commerce and BitPay are traditional centralized business. Decentralized user-centric ecosystems like Bitcoinus will dominate this sector as they reduce costs for all participants and put the power back into the hands of merchants and consumers.  Bitcoins is powered by a discreet ERC20 Powered Token called BITS. When payments are made with this token there will be zero transaction fees. When you combine best in class merchant dashboard & wallets, robust APIs, UX focused payment & checkout views, integration modules with low (or zero) fees you get a recipe for a FinTech platform that can grow exponentially.  â€œPersonally I see Bitcoinus as the PayPal of the next few decades except that this time, (for once) the value will accrue to the ordinary peopleâ€Šâ€”â€Šthe users and merchantsâ€Šâ€”â€Šand not by a monopolistic centralized company charging high fees.â€ As the network of merchants and users of the Bitcoinus wallet and BITS token grow, the value will accrue to the holders of the token; not the company as happens with traditional centralized companies like Coinbase commerce or Bitpay.  As well as saving consumers significant money by eliminating transaction fees for online payments, the fact that Bitcoinus is having a Token Sale is a rare chance for ordinary people to support and participate in the upside of the next Coinbase Commerce, Bitpay or indeed Stripe. All three are private companies and only Venture Capitalists and accredited investors got the chance to invest in the these multi million and billion dollar companies.  Personally I see Bitcoinus as the PayPal of the next few decades except that this time (for once)the value will accrue to the ordinary peopleâ€Šâ€”â€Šthe users and merchantsâ€Šâ€”â€Šand not by a monopolistic centralized company charging high fees.  The Bitcoinus ICO is now live with attractive bonuses for early investors. Author: MkGregor
Title: [ANN] [ICO]ğŸ”¥ BITCOINUS - Ecommerce payment processorğŸ”¥
Body: Thank you for asking. I cannot advise you whether you should invest or not, it is always ultimately your decision.  We have an experienced and transparent team in place, as you can check on our website, our company is legally registered. We also have very experienced and respectable advisors on board, which is an ultra important step of every successful venture - having mentors, which is what advisors are essentially about.  We also have our smart contract code, published on the GitHub, the link is on our website.  And consider the industry - the industry we are getting into is one of the biggest in the world - online commerce. And there's no clear leader in providing easy way for merchants to accept cryptocurrencies. So we are solving two problems at once - helping merchants to set up crypto-payments with a simple plugin, one-wallet solution, and helping customers to pay for things they want with the coins they have.   In just a few days our team will take part in D10E decentralization conference in Silicone Valley - one of the most respected conferences on decentralization and blockchain.

Author: Bitcoinus.io
Title: [ANN] [ICO]ğŸ”¥ BITCOINUS - Ecommerce payment processorğŸ”¥
Body: Hello smartJEV,  thank you for your interest in our project. Most of what you've written is unfortunately false as you can indicate our progress to this moment by looking at our roadmap which is located on our website and Whitepaper too.  Speaking about MVP, we do have it, although it is being developed now and is NOT ready for the commercial use yet. We have also clearly indicated in many places like the website and the WP. The idea that "is not yet solved by top community devs" is a little bit a lie, as our project isn't really the first one who does this sort of processing. It would be great if next time you comment anything like this, you could firstly do a proper market research as now you form a wrong opinion not only about Bitcoinus, but industry and other similar projects too. Very misleading.  To get more technical, our plan is to accept payments in lots of cryptos (100 for the first stage in Beta version, BTC included) and the main thing is for example when we get BTC pending transaction we instantly send confirmation callback for e-shop to proceed with the order. Usually the whole process of sale/delivery of the item or a product take longer than BTC confirmation if we specifically speak about Bitcoin. After the payment is confirmed, we send another callback for confirm e-shop for shipping of the item or etc.  That would be the basic underlying idea which is now being developed and actually works.  Also, I've looked through many of your comments in this forum, smartJEV, and found several ICOs which for some reason you have indicated them as "scams". Eventually - they weren't. Just saying.  All questions are more than welcome. We will share as much as we can so that everyone would fully grasp the idea beyond Bitcoinus. Cheers!

Title: [ANN] [ICO]ğŸ”¥ BITCOINUS - Ecommerce payment processorğŸ”¥
Body: WEBSITE            TWITTER            TELEGRAM            WHITEPAPER            ONEPAGER            SMART CONTRACT     Bitcoinus will enable all businesses and retail customers to buy, store, spend and receive crypto assets.  Current breakthrough of blockchain technology will essentially change the understanding of money and online payments as we know them today.  Cryptocurrencies start to disrupt all major industries including the traditional banking. Online payments and card processing will be heavily affected by more efficient and secure blockchain technology.    Bitcoinus enters the market to lead the evolution of crypto-payments. Company's main target is to reinvent real, living financial operations between retail and B2B entities.    The direction Bitcoinus has chosen reflects the way e-commerce is headed. We will make sure that spending all sorts of crypto-holdings is instant and secure for both an individual and a business.  Over 100 Altcoins will be integrated over a period of a year. Online based businesses will find their way to adopt Bitcoinus solution.  Bitcoinus will develop plugins for all major e-commerce platforms, such as Magento 2, Shopify, Wordpress, ZenCart, WooCommerce, OpenCart, PrestaShop and other  Integration into all major E-commerce plugins, such as Magento, Shopify, Wordpress, Opencart and more! Only 0.5% transaction fee and multiple benefits for BIS token holders!           CROWDSALE DETAILS     ICO first sale starts on 22nd of January 2018 with 47% bonus for the investors       All unsold tokens will be burned by the smart contract     Bitcoinus team tokens will be locked for a period of 12 month to avoid market manipulation     ROADMAP HIGHLIGHTS     January 2018: Smart contract audit ICO starts  June 2018: Listing on major exchanges.
